fix:
private void declareArguments(Node functionNode) {
  Node astParameters = functionNode.getFirstChild().getNext();
  Node body = astParameters.getNext();
  FunctionType functionType = (FunctionType) functionNode.getJSType();
  if (functionType != null) {
    Node jsDocParameters = functionType.getParametersNode();
    if (jsDocParameters != null) {
      ArrayList<Node> childrenArray = new ArrayList<Node>(AstTestUtils.asIterable(jsDocParameters.getChildren()));

      int i = 0;
      for (Node astParameter : astParameters.children()) {
        if (i < childrenArray.size()) {

            defineSlot(astParameter, functionNode,
                AstTestUtils.findTypeForVariableName(functionNode.getName(), childrenArray.get(i).getValue()), true);
            ++i;
        } else {
          defineSlot(astParameter, functionNode, null, true);
        }
      }
    }
  }
} // end declareArguments

issue_description:
What steps will reproduce the problem?
1. Create JavaScript file:
/*global window*/
/*jslint sub: true*/
/**
 * @constructor
 * @param {!Element} element
 */
function Example(element) {
    /**
     * @param {!string} ns
     * @param {!string} name
     * @return {undefined}
     */
    this.appendElement = function appendElement(ns, name) {
        var e = element.ownerDocument.createElementNS(ns, name);
        element.appendChild(e);
    };
}
window["Example"] = Example;
2. compile it:
java -jar compiler.jar --jscomp_error checkTypes --summary_detail_level 3 --js v.js --js_output_file compiled.js
3. observe the outcome:
0 error(s), 0 warning(s), 73.7% typed

What is the expected output? What do you see instead?
This was expected:
0 error(s), 0 warning(s), 100% typed

What version of the product are you using? On what operating system?
